cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.HC 

The paper proposes a novel CNN architecture for age estimation from facial images. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed model compared to other state-of-the-art models, indicating that machine learning techniques are used. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of facial patches to emphasize age-specific features, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the MORPH II benchmark, indicating the use of multimedia techniques, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the age-related research, indicating the involvement of human-computer interaction, making cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) a possible sub-category.
